title: Official website of the President of Ukraine
snippet: ... In Warsaw, President of Ukraine Volodymyr Zelenskyy held a meeting with President of Poland Karol Nawrocki. This was the first official visit by a foreign leader to the incumbent Polish President since his inauguration in August this year.

title: President of Ukraine - Wikipedia
snippet: The current president is Volodymyr Zelenskyy, who took the oath of office on 20 May 2019. Due to martial law, elections in the country have been suspended. title: List of presidents of Ukraine - Wikipedia
snippet: Early presidential elections were held on 25 May 2014 and won by Petro Poroshenko; Poroshenko was inaugurated as the fifth president on 7 June 2014. On 18 June 2015, Yanukovych was officially deprived of the title of President of Ukraine.
